1
00:00:15,700 --> 00:00:19,700
Synched by ShooCat

2
00:00:59,800 --> 00:01:01,800
Come out, come out,
wherever you are!

3
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:03,500
Come on, Ben!

4
00:01:03,700 --> 00:01:04,700
Vincent!

5
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:05,900
Hurry up!

6
00:01:11,900 --> 00:01:13,800
Vincent, what are you doing?

7
00:01:18,800 --> 00:01:19,700
Vincent!

8
00:01:22,600 --> 00:01:23,600
Okay, Ben.

9
00:01:23,800 --> 00:01:24,700
You won!

10
00:01:28,600 --> 00:01:29,800
Vincent?

11
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:38,700
Admit it.
You're looking forward to this.

12
00:01:38,900 --> 00:01:43,100
I got the weekend crowd.
They're not even going to notice.

13
00:01:47,100 --> 00:01:48,200
Give me a break, Ben.

14
00:01:48,500 --> 00:01:50,400
You're the one that wants to go.

15
00:01:51,800 --> 00:01:52,800
Vincent!

16
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:09,100
Vincent!

17
00:02:13,100 --> 00:02:14,500
Ben! You little jerk!

18
00:02:14,800 --> 00:02:16,900
Did you get in
and the lid shut on you?

19
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:21,000
-We go now?
-Yeah, right. We go now.

20
00:02:22,800 --> 00:02:26,600
You'll probably play pool with Joey
after you close the restaurant.

21
00:02:26,900 --> 00:02:29,600
If you're dumb enough to take three
kids to your class reunion...

22
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:31,500
I'm smart enough
to have a good time.

23
00:02:31,700 --> 00:02:34,000
-Hey, party!
-Party hearty!

24
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:38,600
Ben!

25
00:02:38,900 --> 00:02:41,000
-I'm underwater!
-That's great news.

26
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:43,400
Where's your brother?

27
00:02:43,600 --> 00:02:44,400
I don't know.

28
00:02:44,700 --> 00:02:46,700
Will you go find Vincent, please?

29
00:02:49,300 --> 00:02:50,900
Did you remember the sandwiches?

30
00:02:51,100 --> 00:02:52,700
Of course not.

31
00:02:52,900 --> 00:02:55,300
Bethie, if your head wasn't
screwed on...

32
00:02:55,600 --> 00:02:57,900
You'd find it sitting by the microwave.

33
00:02:58,200 --> 00:03:00,100
Then I'd have to call you in Chicago.

34
00:03:00,300 --> 00:03:02,800
Who needs a head
at a high-school reunion?

35
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:05,300
I want to stay with Dad
and go to the restaurant.

36
00:03:05,600 --> 00:03:06,800
I'm not going to Chicago!

37
00:03:07,100 --> 00:03:08,300
You're going!

38
00:03:11,600 --> 00:03:13,800
I hate Ben, I hate Kerry...

39
00:03:14,100 --> 00:03:15,300
and I hate....

40
00:03:15,900 --> 00:03:17,600
Let me finish out the roll.

41
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:18,700
Pat, now?

42
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:19,900
Just two shots!

43
00:03:20,100 --> 00:03:23,000
By the lilacs.
It'll take just a second.

44
00:03:25,700 --> 00:03:27,500
All right, look at Daddy.

45
00:03:27,700 --> 00:03:31,400
I know, the photographer hates
having her picture taken.

46
00:03:31,600 --> 00:03:33,100
Everybody say...

47
00:03:33,500 --> 00:03:34,500
meatball!

48
00:04:03,200 --> 00:04:04,000
Benbo...

49
00:04:04,300 --> 00:04:05,400
bologna is for eating...

50
00:04:05,600 --> 00:04:07,000
not washing windows.

51
00:04:08,200 --> 00:04:09,600
Your seat belt's loose.

52
00:04:10,200 --> 00:04:11,200
Mom, sing me...

53
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:13,300
that bunny song.

54
00:04:13,500 --> 00:04:16,200
I wish I was still home with Dad.

55
00:04:16,500 --> 00:04:19,100
Sing me,
lf a bunny catch a bunny

56
00:04:19,400 --> 00:04:21,600
If a bunny catch a bunny

57
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:25,500
-Coming through the rye
-I hate this song!

58
00:04:25,800 --> 00:04:26,700
If a bunny...

59
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,300
kiss a bunny

60
00:04:28,900 --> 00:04:30,600
And made a bunny cry

61
00:04:54,300 --> 00:04:55,600
You're here.

62
00:04:55,900 --> 00:04:57,200
I'm here!

63
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:01,700
Just a second, let me get Kerry.

64
00:05:01,900 --> 00:05:03,200
No, no. Let me get her.

65
00:05:04,700 --> 00:05:06,400
Look at her!

66
00:05:07,300 --> 00:05:08,900
Watch your head, Benbo.

67
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:12,100
I'm your godmama, Kerry.

68
00:05:12,300 --> 00:05:13,500
Remember me?

69
00:05:13,700 --> 00:05:16,400
God love her! Look at her.

70
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:17,500
My God!

71
00:05:17,800 --> 00:05:19,000
Is that Ben?

72
00:05:19,900 --> 00:05:21,400
Ben! You're a grown-up.

73
00:05:21,700 --> 00:05:23,300
Vincent, can you swim?

74
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:24,800
Martha's inside, waiting for you.

75
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:26,900
Come on, sweetie.

76
00:05:27,100 --> 00:05:28,200
I have a surprise!

77
00:05:28,400 --> 00:05:29,300
Where's your tooth?

78
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:31,100
I lost it.

79
00:05:31,300 --> 00:05:32,300
Speak of the devil!

80
00:05:33,300 --> 00:05:36,300
Beth, you remember Martha,
the babysitter from God.

81
00:05:36,500 --> 00:05:38,100
Great! Can you help with Kerry?

82
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:39,700
Sure thing, Mrs. Cappadora.

83
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:40,900
Mrs. Cappadora.

84
00:05:41,100 --> 00:05:42,300
Good Christ!

85
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:50,600
Is there some kind of
registration table?

86
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:52,900
You're set.
I stuck it on my card.

87
00:05:53,100 --> 00:05:54,800
Ellen, you can't do that!

88
00:05:55,100 --> 00:05:57,100
It's 70 bucks. Who cares?

89
00:05:57,300 --> 00:05:59,000
Donna Trump, I care.

90
00:05:59,200 --> 00:06:00,400
Besides, I can write it off.

91
00:06:00,600 --> 00:06:02,700
I've got a fashion shoot on Sunday.

92
00:06:03,100 --> 00:06:05,100
Boutique on Oak Street.

93
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:09,400
You'll have to go up in
that mess and rearrange it, then.

94
00:06:11,900 --> 00:06:12,800
Oh, Jesus!

95
00:06:13,100 --> 00:06:15,300
Is that Michelle Pulliam?

96
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:16,900
Did she ever marry that guy?

97
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:18,800
They broke up.
Then she went out with...

98
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:22,000
-Elizabeth Kerry and her merry band!
-Jimmy!

99
00:06:23,400 --> 00:06:25,000
How're my big guys?

100
00:06:25,200 --> 00:06:26,100
Wow! Vincent!

101
00:06:26,500 --> 00:06:28,500
You have gotten so huge!

102
00:06:29,300 --> 00:06:32,000
They'd hug any man with a badge,
and so would I.

103
00:06:32,700 --> 00:06:34,800
What would you do if you
found out I made detective?

104
00:06:35,800 --> 00:06:37,400
Congratulations!

105
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:39,300
Guess who I just saw?

106
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:40,800
Cecil Lockhart.

107
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:43,000
You mean Cecilia Lockhart?

108
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:46,800
Star of stage, screen
and mouthwash commercials.

109
00:06:47,800 --> 00:06:49,500
My God! There she is.

110
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:51,900
Remember when she first got laid?

111
00:06:52,200 --> 00:06:54,000
When she was 15, and she told us:

112
00:06:55,200 --> 00:06:58,000
"I can't imagine
going a month without it".

113
00:06:59,700 --> 00:07:01,800
She was talking about pizza, guys.

114
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:03,000
Hey, Beth!

115
00:07:03,300 --> 00:07:05,300
My God! How are you?

116
00:07:05,500 --> 00:07:08,400
-Look at you! How are you?
-Good, good.

117
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:09,600
Is this your new one?

118
00:07:11,400 --> 00:07:12,500
Where's little Vincent?

119
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:14,000
I'm not little.

120
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:15,600
No, you're not.

121
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:18,000
-Sandy! Bye...
-Mom, I want to go.

122
00:07:18,200 --> 00:07:19,300
I want pizza!

123
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:21,700
You stay with your brother.

124
00:07:21,900 --> 00:07:24,700
Martha, would you take care of the car?

125
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:26,700
-I'll handle it.
-I'll pay the thing.

126
00:07:36,700 --> 00:07:37,500
Vincent?

127
00:07:38,100 --> 00:07:41,300
Listen. I want you to hold
Ben's hand real tight.

128
00:07:41,500 --> 00:07:44,900
And you guys can play
on this really cool cart, okay?

129
00:07:46,400 --> 00:07:47,800
Mom, my neck's hot.

130
00:07:48,100 --> 00:07:49,500
My neck's killing me.

131
00:07:49,700 --> 00:07:50,700
Vincent, listen.

132
00:07:50,900 --> 00:07:52,500
This'll only take a second.

133
00:07:52,900 --> 00:07:55,000
Stay here with Ben while I
pay the lady.

134
00:07:55,300 --> 00:07:57,400
When Martha comes,
she'll take you swimming, okay?

135
00:08:16,900 --> 00:08:17,800
Thanks.

136
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:20,800
-Sorry it took so long.
-That's okay.

137
00:08:28,500 --> 00:08:30,100
Where's Ben?

138
00:08:30,300 --> 00:08:32,400
He wouldn't let me hold him.
Would you look at my neck?

139
00:08:32,700 --> 00:08:34,800
I've got a heat rash or something.

140
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:36,500
Hold on, sweetie.

141
00:08:41,500 --> 00:08:42,300
Ben?

142
00:08:47,700 --> 00:08:48,600
Ellen?

143
00:08:48,900 --> 00:08:51,200
Ben took off. Would you...?

144
00:08:51,400 --> 00:08:53,300
I'll find him.
See you later.

145
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:56,800
You stay here. Don't move.

146
00:08:58,600 --> 00:08:59,500
Ben?

147
00:09:14,300 --> 00:09:15,600
Have you seen a little boy?

148
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:18,400
He's got a red baseball cap,
3 years old.

149
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:19,400
No, sorry.

150
00:09:20,100 --> 00:09:21,300
Thanks.

151
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:25,700
Ben?

152
00:09:40,800 --> 00:09:42,000
Excuse me.

153
00:09:45,400 --> 00:09:46,300
Vincent...

154
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:47,700
think hard.

155
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:49,600
Which way did Ben go?

156
00:09:49,800 --> 00:09:51,300
I don't know.

157
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:52,300
Didn't you watch?

158
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:54,900
I couldn't see him.

159
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:57,500
He wasn't over there.

160
00:09:57,700 --> 00:09:59,000
We should get the manager.

161
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:00,500
I don't know.

162
00:10:00,700 --> 00:10:02,500
Maybe if we just wait....

163
00:10:18,100 --> 00:10:19,000
Stop!

164
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:21,800
Everybody please just
listen up for a second.

165
00:10:22,400 --> 00:10:25,200
We need to look for
Beth Kerry's little boy.

166
00:10:25,400 --> 00:10:26,900
His name is Ben.

167
00:10:27,100 --> 00:10:30,300
He's 3, he was wearing
a red baseball cap.

168
00:10:30,500 --> 00:10:32,100
He was just here a second ago.

169
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:34,500
So if you'd look around
where you are.

170
00:10:34,800 --> 00:10:35,800
Wait. Hold on, folks.

171
00:10:36,100 --> 00:10:37,700
We'll find him.
It's going to be fine.

172
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:40,900
I'm going to divide the room
down the middle.

173
00:10:41,100 --> 00:10:44,000
I want you to stay
in your half and look around you.

174
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:45,300
If you see Ben...

175
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:48,200
pick him up and call out
to me, all right?

176
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:05,400
Pat will be here soon, right?

177
00:11:06,900 --> 00:11:08,400
I didn't call him.

178
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:13,100
I thought we'd find Ben right away.

179
00:11:14,200 --> 00:11:16,400
Let's make that call now, right?

180
00:11:26,400 --> 00:11:27,700
Here you go.

181
00:11:29,400 --> 00:11:30,800
Go ahead, Beth.

182
00:11:33,500 --> 00:11:34,700
-Hello?
-Patty!

183
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:50,500
Magill, talk to the female.

184
00:11:50,700 --> 00:11:52,500
Coleman, come with me.

185
00:11:55,500 --> 00:11:56,400
Mrs. Cappadora?

186
00:11:56,700 --> 00:11:58,000
I'm Officer Magill.

187
00:11:59,200 --> 00:12:00,700
You brought a lot of officers.

188
00:12:01,400 --> 00:12:04,400
We take the disappearance of a
child very seriously.

189
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:08,000
You're worried, then?

190
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:09,900
We'll find him.

191
00:12:10,100 --> 00:12:11,400
Lost kids,
we always find them.

192
00:12:12,100 --> 00:12:13,400
And they're okay.

193
00:12:13,600 --> 00:12:15,100
-They're not hurt.
-Good.

194
00:12:15,400 --> 00:12:18,500
If it gets to five hours,
we usually consider it....

195
00:12:19,500 --> 00:12:22,200
Anyway, we'll find him before then.

196
00:12:27,900 --> 00:12:29,700
So your friend Elaine was with you?

197
00:12:30,800 --> 00:12:31,800
Ellen.

198
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:34,600
She met me out front.
She was waiting for me.

199
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:38,700
Besides Ellen, who was
the first person you talked to?

200
00:12:40,600 --> 00:12:41,500
The cheerleaders.

201
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:44,300
Would another family member...

202
00:12:44,600 --> 00:12:47,000
on your side have any reason
to pick up the boy?

203
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:49,100
My folks are dead.

204
00:12:49,500 --> 00:12:50,600
There's nobody.

205
00:12:50,900 --> 00:12:52,800
Has he ever been fingerprinted?

206
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:54,300
No.

207
00:12:55,300 --> 00:12:56,200
Yes!

208
00:12:56,700 --> 00:12:59,400
The school district had a program.

209
00:13:09,100 --> 00:13:10,300
It's been four hours.

210
00:13:10,600 --> 00:13:12,600
We've got everybody on it, okay?

211
00:13:13,100 --> 00:13:16,100
This is my boss,
Detective Supervisor Bliss.

212
00:13:16,900 --> 00:13:18,800
-Bliss?
-Candy Bliss.

213
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:21,300
It sounds like a stripper's name.

214
00:13:21,500 --> 00:13:23,300
The things parents do to kids!

215
00:13:24,500 --> 00:13:26,400
I can't believe I said that.

216
00:13:26,700 --> 00:13:29,200
We'll do everything we can
to find your boy.

217
00:13:29,500 --> 00:13:30,300
Description out?

218
00:13:30,500 --> 00:13:32,000
They're checking the database now.

219
00:13:32,300 --> 00:13:33,100
Great.

220
00:13:33,600 --> 00:13:36,500
First, I want to tell you this is
nobody's fault.

221
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:40,200
Kids disappear all the time,
and somebody always finds them.

222
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:41,400
That's right.

223
00:13:41,900 --> 00:13:43,500
We're set up over here.

224
00:13:52,600 --> 00:13:53,600
Where is he?

225
00:13:53,800 --> 00:13:56,000
My son! Where is he?

226
00:13:56,300 --> 00:13:57,600
We haven't found him yet...

227
00:13:57,800 --> 00:13:59,200
Where's Ben?

228
00:13:59,500 --> 00:14:00,500
Where's Bethie?

229
00:14:00,700 --> 00:14:01,700
Bethie?

230
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:03,200
Pat!

231
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:11,400
How did this happen?

232
00:14:12,800 --> 00:14:14,200
Okay, all right, okay.

233
00:14:14,400 --> 00:14:15,500
It'll be okay.

234
00:14:15,700 --> 00:14:17,400
Where is it nobody's searched?

235
00:14:17,700 --> 00:14:18,700
The basement?

236
00:14:18,900 --> 00:14:21,700
It's just food storage.
All the doors are kept locked.

237
00:14:21,900 --> 00:14:23,700
But you have freezers, cabinets?

238
00:14:24,300 --> 00:14:26,800
Ben loves hiding places.
Take me down there.

239
00:14:30,300 --> 00:14:31,200
You okay?

240
00:14:31,400 --> 00:14:32,500
You sure?

241
00:14:32,800 --> 00:14:36,300
I'm going downstairs a minute.
You stay here with Mommy, okay?

242
00:14:37,100 --> 00:14:38,200
Let's go.

243
00:14:55,600 --> 00:14:56,600
Mom!

244
00:14:56,900 --> 00:14:58,000
Patty!

245
00:14:58,200 --> 00:14:59,900
Are you all right?

246
00:15:03,900 --> 00:15:06,600
My God in heaven!
How long has he been missing?

247
00:15:06,900 --> 00:15:08,700
About five hours.

248
00:15:10,500 --> 00:15:12,900
They'll remember.
They'll make one more call.

249
00:15:13,200 --> 00:15:14,700
I'll take you to the command center.

250
00:15:14,900 --> 00:15:16,400
Kerry and Vincent will come...

251
00:15:16,600 --> 00:15:17,800
to the house. It's better, right?

252
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:20,200
-Where's Kerry?
-Upstairs.

253
00:15:20,700 --> 00:15:22,500
You'll come with Grandma, honey.

254
00:15:23,400 --> 00:15:25,400
You go with Grandma, Vincent, okay?

255
00:15:35,400 --> 00:15:38,700
Will you tell me when
Ben gets back, Mom?

256
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:40,100
She'll tell us.

257
00:15:40,300 --> 00:15:41,800
Sit down, sweetheart.

258
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:45,700
I'm sorry.

259
00:15:45,900 --> 00:15:48,100
Do you have any other pictures of Ben?

260
00:15:49,200 --> 00:15:50,300
I lost my purse.

261
00:15:50,500 --> 00:15:52,500
No, no, no.
I have it, honey.

262
00:16:09,400 --> 00:16:10,800
Ben!

263
00:16:11,800 --> 00:16:13,900
Bethie, honey, it's okay.

264
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:17,900
Set her down!

265
00:16:18,300 --> 00:16:20,200
I want Ben!

266
00:16:20,500 --> 00:16:23,000
Grab her wrist and hold her down.
Medic!

267
00:16:23,200 --> 00:16:24,600
It's okay. It's all right.

268
00:16:26,700 --> 00:16:27,800
Give her something!

269
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:29,100
Quick!

270
00:16:30,800 --> 00:16:32,700
It's all right, sweetheart.
It's all right.

271
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:36,900
I know, Bethie. I know.

272
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:39,600
You don't know.

273
00:16:39,900 --> 00:16:41,600
I don't even know.

274
00:16:54,800 --> 00:16:56,700
How long are you
staying with your parents?

275
00:16:56,900 --> 00:16:58,500
Do the police have leads?

276
00:16:58,800 --> 00:17:00,900
Have the kidnappers
tried to contact you?

277
00:17:01,400 --> 00:17:04,000
How long were you gone before you
noticed your son was missing?

278
00:17:04,300 --> 00:17:08,000
-Who'd want to do this?
-How long will you be in Chicago?

279
00:17:09,200 --> 00:17:11,000
He's 3 years old...

280
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:12,600
but he's big for his age.

281
00:17:12,800 --> 00:17:15,100
And people always think he's older.

282
00:17:15,300 --> 00:17:17,700
He's very verbal.

283
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:20,500
He babbles to himself.

284
00:17:20,900 --> 00:17:23,100
Sometimes you can barely hear him...

285
00:17:23,300 --> 00:17:26,400
but he says his words very clearly.

286
00:17:27,200 --> 00:17:29,500
He has blond hair and blue eyes.

287
00:17:29,700 --> 00:17:30,700
And he was wearing...

288
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:32,500
a red baseball cap.

289
00:17:32,700 --> 00:17:35,200
And he loves pizza.

290
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:40,500
He's very afraid of the water.

291
00:17:42,500 --> 00:17:43,400
He loves...

292
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:45,400
to sing songs.

293
00:17:45,600 --> 00:17:48,800
Sometimes he'll sing the same song
over and over again.

294
00:17:50,100 --> 00:17:51,300
He was wearing...

295
00:17:55,300 --> 00:17:57,000
red shoes.

296
00:17:57,300 --> 00:18:00,500
High-top sneakers with
green parrots on the side.

297
00:18:00,700 --> 00:18:03,000
And white socks.

298
00:18:04,700 --> 00:18:07,400
And a red T-shirt...

299
00:18:07,600 --> 00:18:09,500
 with yellow sleeves...

300
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:13,800
and little blue shorts.
Blue plaid shorts.

301
00:18:16,400 --> 00:18:18,100
Call you when we get home.

302
00:18:50,100 --> 00:18:51,900
Unbelievable, right?

303
00:18:52,900 --> 00:18:54,400
Diane Lundgren's on her way over...

304
00:18:54,600 --> 00:18:56,600
and Cecil Lockhart signed up.

305
00:18:57,900 --> 00:18:59,800
But her mother got sick.

306
00:19:00,600 --> 00:19:01,900
You know who else called?

307
00:19:02,100 --> 00:19:03,700
Lizzy De Nunzio.

308
00:19:04,000 --> 00:19:06,900
-Where is she now, Switzerland?
-I think she moved there.

309
00:19:07,100 --> 00:19:09,600
-How'd she even find out about it?
-Who knows?

310
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:12,100
But she just sounds sick about it.

311
00:19:12,800 --> 00:19:14,800
-Everyone is, Bethie.
-I know.

312
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:16,100
I know.

313
00:19:16,400 --> 00:19:17,800
Laurie!

314
00:19:18,700 --> 00:19:19,700
I can't believe you're here.

315
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:23,300
What was I supposed to do?
Stay in Madison? Watch CNN?

316
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:20,300
Hey, Tommy.

317
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:22,600
Have you seen Candy?

318
00:20:22,900 --> 00:20:25,300
-She's with McGuire.
-Thanks, Ricky.

319
00:20:26,800 --> 00:20:29,000
Then go to Minneapolis.
How far can it be?

320
00:20:29,200 --> 00:20:31,100
We've been getting
bogus leads...

321
00:20:31,300 --> 00:20:34,600
every day for six weeks now.
This kid is dead and you know it.

322
00:20:34,900 --> 00:20:37,300
Don't tell me I know it!
I don't know it.

323
00:20:37,600 --> 00:20:39,800
This is interstate.
I have to call the FBI.

324
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:42,100
Come on, Candy, the FBI?

325
00:20:42,400 --> 00:20:44,000
Give me a break.

326
00:20:46,300 --> 00:20:47,600
Hey, Bethie.

327
00:20:48,200 --> 00:20:49,500
So you heard that?

328
00:20:49,700 --> 00:20:52,300
I heard something about the FBI.

329
00:20:52,600 --> 00:20:54,200
Come into my office.

330
00:20:56,500 --> 00:20:57,700
Have a seat.

331
00:21:02,800 --> 00:21:04,000
Listen, Beth.

332
00:21:04,200 --> 00:21:06,400
Just because volunteers
are going home...

333
00:21:06,600 --> 00:21:08,300
doesn't mean the case is closed.

334
00:21:08,700 --> 00:21:10,200
Some of them got lives.

335
00:21:10,400 --> 00:21:11,500
I don't.

336
00:21:11,700 --> 00:21:13,000
So I'm here.

337
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:15,000
And I'm not giving up.

338
00:21:21,600 --> 00:21:23,500
I'm sorry, I didn't...

339
00:21:25,600 --> 00:21:26,600
I'm a jerk.

340
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:29,900
There's nothing wrong
with what you just did.

341
00:21:30,100 --> 00:21:31,800
I'm just an oversensitive jerk.

342
00:21:32,100 --> 00:21:33,300
You're too involved. You can't...

343
00:21:34,200 --> 00:21:35,200
I'm black.

344
00:21:35,500 --> 00:21:37,900
I'm a woman.
I'm a detective supervisor.

345
00:21:38,200 --> 00:21:40,800
And I'm gay.
Did you know that?

346
00:21:41,100 --> 00:21:44,100
I always feel like the eyes
of Texas are on me.

347
00:21:44,400 --> 00:21:47,100
Every time I hug Katie
from Crime Stoppers...

348
00:21:47,400 --> 00:21:49,200
I think she thinks
I'm coming on to her.

349
00:21:49,500 --> 00:21:50,300
I wasn't...

350
00:21:50,500 --> 00:21:51,900
No, I know that.

351
00:21:52,200 --> 00:21:56,100
I just wanted you to know
I'm a little jerkish today.

352
00:21:56,900 --> 00:21:59,500
So that calls for a Gummi Bear.

353
00:22:00,500 --> 00:22:02,600
Tough guys chew Gummi Bears.

354
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:07,900
Beth, you laughed.

355
00:22:08,400 --> 00:22:10,400
You only laughed.

356
00:22:12,300 --> 00:22:15,000
It doesn't mean our side loses points.

357
00:22:15,200 --> 00:22:18,700
It doesn't mean you'll
kill your son because you laughed.

358
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:21,700
You have got to survive.

359
00:22:23,900 --> 00:22:25,200
That's just it.

360
00:22:26,400 --> 00:22:28,900
I don't want to survive Ben.

361
00:22:31,600 --> 00:22:33,500
I don't want to face it.

362
00:22:33,800 --> 00:22:35,300
Then I guess you can just...

363
00:22:35,500 --> 00:22:39,300
move into a corner in my office,
and I'll use you as a coat rack.

364
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:41,900
You got to do whatever you got to do.

365
00:22:42,100 --> 00:22:46,300
But you got two great kids, which I
would give my right arm for.

366
00:22:46,800 --> 00:22:48,900
Though you think
you're a terrible mother...

367
00:22:49,200 --> 00:22:51,500
you're the only mother they have.

368
00:22:56,900 --> 00:22:58,600
I should go home.

369
00:23:38,400 --> 00:23:40,700
Jill's been great with Kerry.

370
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:42,000
Really great.

371
00:23:43,800 --> 00:23:46,800
But I think Vincent's
going to need a little time.

372
00:23:47,400 --> 00:23:50,500
He'll be fine.
He's been back, what, six weeks?

373
00:23:51,900 --> 00:23:54,200
I'm sure he'll be fine.

374
00:24:23,100 --> 00:24:23,900
Coming?

375
00:24:36,500 --> 00:24:37,900
Jill, we're back!

376
00:24:47,100 --> 00:24:48,600
Baby, you scared me.

377
00:24:48,900 --> 00:24:50,900
How's my big guy?

378
00:24:51,100 --> 00:24:52,500
Are you good?

379
00:24:52,700 --> 00:24:53,600
Mom, guess what?

380
00:24:53,900 --> 00:24:57,600
On Thursday, I made
six baskets in a row!

381
00:24:58,300 --> 00:25:00,600
Look how long your legs are.

382
00:26:34,900 --> 00:26:36,800
How is she?
Has she been in bed all day?

383
00:26:37,000 --> 00:26:37,800
Pretty much.

384
00:26:38,100 --> 00:26:40,400
How'd Vincent get home?
Did you pick him up?

385
00:26:40,600 --> 00:26:42,600
Yeah, I didn't have class today.

386
00:26:42,800 --> 00:26:43,800
Okay, thanks.

387
00:26:44,100 --> 00:26:46,000
Did she say
she was coming down?

388
00:26:46,300 --> 00:26:47,100
No, she didn't.

389
00:26:47,700 --> 00:26:50,200
So some girl walks in, chewing gum...

390
00:26:50,400 --> 00:26:51,900
and talking through her nose...

391
00:26:52,200 --> 00:26:54,000
has legs up to her neck.

392
00:26:54,300 --> 00:26:56,500
Paolo just says,
"Great, you're hired!"

393
00:26:56,900 --> 00:26:57,900
The new kids we got...

394
00:26:58,800 --> 00:27:01,000
don't know spaghetti from scampi.

395
00:27:01,700 --> 00:27:05,200
They think the cash register
is their personal savings account.

396
00:27:06,000 --> 00:27:07,100
I'll tell you what...

397
00:27:08,600 --> 00:27:10,500
when I open my own place...

398
00:27:10,800 --> 00:27:13,200
this is exactly what you won't see.

399
00:27:38,500 --> 00:27:39,600
Guess what happened.

400
00:27:39,800 --> 00:27:41,800
I thought today was Sunday.

401
00:27:42,700 --> 00:27:44,100
Isn't that funny?

402
00:27:45,100 --> 00:27:46,900
Can we just please go?

403
00:29:37,900 --> 00:29:39,600
I'm going to work, honey.

404
00:29:40,000 --> 00:29:41,500
Beth, you downstairs?

405
00:29:54,000 --> 00:29:55,700
Honey, what are you doing?

406
00:30:03,300 --> 00:30:06,400
Ever been in a doctor's office
without a People magazine?

407
00:30:06,700 --> 00:30:10,000
One day, Ben will go to a doctor's
office with whoever took him.

408
00:30:10,300 --> 00:30:13,600
-And some other patient...
-Laurie, stop! Okay?

409
00:30:14,200 --> 00:30:16,700
I know you mean well, but just...

410
00:30:16,900 --> 00:30:18,100
stop.

411
00:30:37,300 --> 00:30:38,800
-That's real leather?
-You bet!

412
00:30:39,100 --> 00:30:41,100
-Thanks, Uncle Joey.
-You're welcome.

413
00:30:41,300 --> 00:30:43,000
Check this out, buddy.

414
00:30:48,200 --> 00:30:49,900
Could be more presents.

415
00:30:50,900 --> 00:30:52,400
Merry Christmas!

416
00:30:52,900 --> 00:30:55,300
Joey, it's cold.
Shut the door.

417
00:30:57,600 --> 00:30:59,500
-Where's the tree?
-Pat went to get it.

418
00:30:59,700 --> 00:31:01,200
Where's my presents?

419
00:31:03,500 --> 00:31:05,000
Merry Christmas, Beth!

420
00:31:06,200 --> 00:31:10,200
Mom, look, Uncle Joey gave me
my stocking present early...

421
00:31:10,400 --> 00:31:12,300
because it's too big
to fit in the stocking.

422
00:31:12,500 --> 00:31:14,700
-See?
-Yeah, that's great!

423
00:31:17,500 --> 00:31:18,400
Merry Christmas, Beth.

424
00:31:18,700 --> 00:31:20,900
-Merry Christmas, Theresa.
-How you feeling, honey?

425
00:31:21,100 --> 00:31:24,100
I almost didn't make it.
I started having Braxton-Hicks.

426
00:31:24,400 --> 00:31:26,300
-You should breathe in a bag.
-I'll try that.

427
00:31:26,600 --> 00:31:28,400
-May be a Christmas baby.
-I hope not.

428
00:31:28,700 --> 00:31:32,100
She's carrying like it's a boy.
That's what everybody says.

429
00:31:33,400 --> 00:31:34,600
The gang's all here!

430
00:31:34,900 --> 00:31:37,900
-My God, sis, look how big you are!
-Don't rub it in.

431
00:31:38,100 --> 00:31:39,400
Patty, it's beautiful!

432
00:31:40,600 --> 00:31:42,900
-Who do you think these are for?
-Me?

433
00:31:44,600 --> 00:31:47,100
One is from me,
and one's from Grandpa Angelo.

434
00:31:47,500 --> 00:31:49,700
-Help me wrap.
-Look at the cards.

435
00:31:49,900 --> 00:31:51,500
Did you buy out
the whole store?

436
00:31:51,700 --> 00:31:53,100
Who's counting?
It's Christmas.

437
00:31:53,400 --> 00:31:55,900
Now, these are very special.

438
00:31:59,600 --> 00:32:02,900
Look, Mom, they're for Ben
from Grandma and Grandpa.

439
00:32:07,400 --> 00:32:09,300
Rosie, what are these?

440
00:32:09,900 --> 00:32:11,500
Presents for Ben.

441
00:32:16,300 --> 00:32:17,700
Why did you bring presents for Ben?

442
00:32:18,100 --> 00:32:20,300
I believe that Ben will be found.

443
00:32:20,600 --> 00:32:24,400
When he is found, I want him to
know his family didn't forget him.

444
00:32:25,600 --> 00:32:27,600
Do you have the impression
we've forgotten Ben?

445
00:32:27,900 --> 00:32:29,400
Of course not.

446
00:32:29,700 --> 00:32:31,800
-We didn't get Ben any gifts.
-I understand that.

447
00:32:32,100 --> 00:32:34,300
I didn't even want to go through...

448
00:32:34,600 --> 00:32:36,800
this whole, big holiday act.

449
00:32:37,100 --> 00:32:40,600
You know what I wanted to do?
I wanted to sleep through it.

450
00:32:40,800 --> 00:32:42,800
When you do this, like he's just...

451
00:32:43,000 --> 00:32:46,700
out of town on some business trip
and he'll be back anytime...

452
00:32:47,000 --> 00:32:48,800
-Beth, take it easy.
-Take it easy!

453
00:32:49,000 --> 00:32:51,300
How can I take it easy
when nobody except me...

454
00:32:51,500 --> 00:32:54,500
seems to want to accept
the fact that it's over?

455
00:32:55,000 --> 00:32:55,900
It's over!

456
00:32:56,100 --> 00:32:58,800
We're all going to go on
eating and sleeping...

457
00:32:59,100 --> 00:33:01,900
You have to snap out of this.
No one can talk to you.

458
00:33:02,200 --> 00:33:03,000
I can't.

459
00:33:03,300 --> 00:33:04,300
-Pat can't.
-Butt out!

460
00:33:04,500 --> 00:33:07,200
If you don't have hope
Ben will come back...

461
00:33:07,500 --> 00:33:09,800
Come back?
He's not even 4 yet.

462
00:33:10,000 --> 00:33:12,700
What's he going to do?
Get an Amtrak schedule?

463
00:33:13,100 --> 00:33:14,800
We didn't mean anything by it.

464
00:33:16,400 --> 00:33:18,900
-Don't you think we're all grieving?
-I mean it!

465
00:33:19,200 --> 00:33:20,300
-Shut up!
-No, Pat!

466
00:33:20,600 --> 00:33:22,800
You're all scared to say this,
but I'm not.

467
00:33:23,100 --> 00:33:25,500
We try and call.
She doesn't want to talk.

468
00:33:25,800 --> 00:33:27,000
We write. She doesn't answer.

469
00:33:27,300 --> 00:33:29,200
Mom, Ben will be back tomorrow.

470
00:33:30,700 --> 00:33:31,600
What?

471
00:33:31,800 --> 00:33:34,100
Because it's Christmas.
For my present...

472
00:33:34,400 --> 00:33:36,000
I asked Santa to bring Ben home.

473
00:33:36,300 --> 00:33:38,400
I think he'll do it.

474
00:33:41,400 --> 00:33:43,300
-Where is she?
-She's upstairs.

475
00:33:43,600 --> 00:33:45,300
She still won't speak to me, will she?

476
00:33:45,600 --> 00:33:47,100
I think she will.

477
00:33:47,300 --> 00:33:49,000
Everybody's been calling.

478
00:33:49,200 --> 00:33:52,400
After your talk with People,
we reprinted the poster five times.

479
00:33:53,100 --> 00:33:55,200
I think she hates my guts.

480
00:34:09,600 --> 00:34:10,800
What are you doing?

481
00:34:11,000 --> 00:34:12,400
Ending world hunger.

482
00:34:12,600 --> 00:34:14,600
I just got off the phone with the U.N.

483
00:34:16,700 --> 00:34:18,000
That's good.

484
00:34:20,300 --> 00:34:22,500
Look, will you just forgive me...

485
00:34:22,700 --> 00:34:24,300
and get this over with?

486
00:34:24,600 --> 00:34:28,300
I'd never give them anything unless
it was the right thing to do.

487
00:34:28,500 --> 00:34:31,700
I would never do a thing to hurt you.

488
00:34:32,700 --> 00:34:34,100
How long have we been friends?

489
00:34:34,900 --> 00:34:37,100
One thousand years.

490
00:34:37,600 --> 00:34:40,200
-I know.
-Then good, okay?

491
00:34:41,300 --> 00:34:43,000
I have something I want you to do.

492
00:34:44,100 --> 00:34:45,800
I don't believe you.

493
00:34:46,800 --> 00:34:50,200
-I want you to take a picture.
-I don't do that anymore.

494
00:34:50,400 --> 00:34:52,500
I took early retirement.

495
00:34:52,700 --> 00:34:54,100
You could use the money.

496
00:34:54,400 --> 00:34:56,100
This is good money.

497
00:34:56,600 --> 00:34:57,500
Good for what?

498
00:34:57,800 --> 00:35:00,000
I want her to take a portrait
of a Chinese family.

499
00:35:00,600 --> 00:35:04,000
We are kind of tapped out,
just keeping Vincent in sneakers.

500
00:35:04,600 --> 00:35:06,000
You could do this.

501
00:35:06,300 --> 00:35:07,600
You wouldn't even have to go out.

502
00:35:12,200 --> 00:35:14,300
I threw away all my paper and stuff.

503
00:35:14,700 --> 00:35:17,000
I'll go get you more paper and stuff.

504
00:35:17,600 --> 00:35:18,600
Please.

505
00:35:19,100 --> 00:35:20,800
Please, just this once.

506
00:35:21,300 --> 00:35:24,400
Let me get rid of my guilt
by doing you this one good turn.

507
00:35:24,600 --> 00:35:27,900
This is not a good turn.
This is a setup.

508
00:36:29,500 --> 00:36:31,200
These are really beautiful.

509
00:36:41,500 --> 00:36:44,600
I have to print.
I have four phone calls to make.

510
00:36:44,900 --> 00:36:47,400
I have to get Vincent
ready for Little League.

511
00:36:47,800 --> 00:36:49,800
Thought any more about Chicago?

512
00:36:50,000 --> 00:36:51,200
What about it?

513
00:36:52,300 --> 00:36:53,600
Could be great.

514
00:36:53,900 --> 00:36:55,400
Kids'll love it there.

515
00:36:55,700 --> 00:36:58,400
-I'll have my own restaurant.
-I have to get Kerry up.

516
00:36:58,700 --> 00:37:01,400
-There's plenty of time for that.
-Okay, fine.

517
00:37:01,700 --> 00:37:05,900
You go upstairs, get my diaphragm,
fill it up with gunk and...

518
00:37:06,100 --> 00:37:09,200
we'll have eight minutes
before I have to feed Vincent.

519
00:37:09,500 --> 00:37:11,700
We can have a lot
of fun in eight minutes.

520
00:37:12,300 --> 00:37:13,700
Fine. You want to do it right here?

521
00:37:13,900 --> 00:37:15,700
I can make toast at the same time.

522
00:37:16,000 --> 00:37:18,600
It's not like I'm on top of you
all the time.

523
00:37:18,800 --> 00:37:21,300
We make love as often
as we pay the water bill.

524
00:37:22,000 --> 00:37:24,300
I don't see why you need
a diaphragm every time.

525
00:37:24,500 --> 00:37:26,900
I don't want to
get pregnant every time.

526
00:37:27,300 --> 00:37:30,900
We had three kids and we always
wanted more. I miss that.

527
00:37:31,200 --> 00:37:32,800
I miss this house being full of noise.

528
00:37:33,000 --> 00:37:35,200
I used to want to
run up the walk to lunch.

529
00:37:36,200 --> 00:37:38,700
It's not going to change anything.

530
00:37:39,100 --> 00:37:41,600
Another kid.
It'd be like a replacement part.

531
00:37:41,900 --> 00:37:44,900
Like you get a new gravy boat
so you don't spoil the set.

532
00:37:45,700 --> 00:37:47,200
That's a lousy fucking thing to say.

533
00:37:47,500 --> 00:37:51,200
I agree. So I'll stop saying
fucking lousy things.

