00:58:21,700 --> 00:58:23,500
We have a warrant
to search the premises.

797
00:58:24,000 --> 00:58:25,800
-Can you step over here?
-This is a mistake.

798
00:58:26,000 --> 00:58:28,700
-You don't have any guns?
-No, I don't.

799
00:58:28,900 --> 00:58:30,900
You won't mind if the officers
search here?

800
00:58:31,100 --> 00:58:34,800
I didn't do anything. This is my house.
I was just doing the books.

801
00:58:35,000 --> 00:58:37,600
I don't even know why
you people are here.

802
00:58:37,900 --> 00:58:39,500
That's Cecil.

803
00:58:42,800 --> 00:58:44,500
That's Cecil Lockhart.

804
00:58:45,300 --> 00:58:47,100
You know her from television?

805
00:58:48,100 --> 00:58:50,200
Why do you have a picture
of Cecil Lockhart?

806
00:58:55,500 --> 00:58:56,700
She was my wife.

807
00:59:01,100 --> 00:59:03,400
Cecil gave birth in 1985...

808
00:59:03,700 --> 00:59:05,900
which is the same year Ben was born.

809
00:59:06,100 --> 00:59:08,900
Apparently, the baby had
complications and died.

810
00:59:09,200 --> 00:59:12,300
She had a nervous breakdown.
They had to put her away.

811
00:59:12,500 --> 00:59:15,400
She got out three years after that,
just in time...

812
00:59:15,700 --> 00:59:19,900
to make it to the reunion,
where she saw Ben and snatched him.

813
00:59:20,100 --> 00:59:21,800
She disappeared into Minneapolis...

814
00:59:22,000 --> 00:59:23,900
where she met George and married him.

815
00:59:24,100 --> 00:59:25,800
He adopted Ben...

816
00:59:26,000 --> 00:59:27,500
and then they moved here.

817
00:59:27,800 --> 00:59:31,200
About five years ago,
she committed suicide.

818
00:59:34,100 --> 00:59:36,500
I got to tell you, I feel...

819
00:59:36,800 --> 00:59:38,700
totally responsible...

820
00:59:39,500 --> 00:59:40,900
for a lot of what's happened.

821
00:59:41,200 --> 00:59:43,300
We interviewed this woman.

822
00:59:43,600 --> 00:59:46,900
I sat in this woman's house.
I had tea with her.

823
00:59:47,200 --> 00:59:49,200
And somewhere in there was Ben...

824
00:59:49,400 --> 00:59:51,100
and I missed him.

825
00:59:52,100 --> 00:59:55,500
George Karras wasn't at all
suspicious, and he adopted Ben.

826
00:59:55,700 --> 00:59:57,500
So she lied to her husband.

827
00:59:57,900 --> 00:59:59,200
She lied to me.

828
00:59:59,900 --> 01:00:03,500
I'm supposed to know when people
are lying because I'm a supercop.

829
01:00:06,400 --> 01:00:08,900
I didn't find him.
You guys did.

830
01:00:09,500 --> 01:00:11,400
No one found him.

831
01:00:11,700 --> 01:00:13,200
He found us.

832
01:00:17,500 --> 01:00:19,300
Are you heading to
the foster home now?

833
01:00:19,600 --> 01:00:21,400
What will you say to him?

834
01:00:21,700 --> 01:00:23,400
How's it feel to get your son back?

835
01:00:23,600 --> 01:00:26,400
Did you contact him at all
in the last two weeks?

836
01:00:27,700 --> 01:00:29,600
Will you call him Ben or Sam?

837
01:00:31,600 --> 01:00:34,000
Do you have any statement to make?

838
01:01:32,400 --> 01:01:33,700
How are you?

839
01:01:35,900 --> 01:01:37,100
I'm good.

840
01:01:41,800 --> 01:01:42,700
Dad?

841
01:01:43,000 --> 01:01:44,400
-Yes?
-Yeah, Sam?

842
01:02:05,800 --> 01:02:06,800
Stop fidgeting.

843
01:02:10,300 --> 01:02:11,500
You're not hungry?

844
01:02:11,800 --> 01:02:12,600
I'm eating.

845
01:02:12,900 --> 01:02:15,600
I'm not an industrial vacuum,
like some people.

846
01:02:25,600 --> 01:02:27,100
Could I have some milk?

847
01:02:27,400 --> 01:02:28,700
You do milk with pizza?

848
01:02:34,800 --> 01:02:36,800
I like milk with pizza.

849
01:02:42,300 --> 01:02:44,700
-Good night, Kerry.
-Good night, Mom.

850
01:02:50,000 --> 01:02:51,300
Do you want the light on?

851
01:02:51,900 --> 01:02:54,200
No, I don't sleep with a light.

852
01:02:56,200 --> 01:02:58,900
Do you want an extra
blanket or anything?

853
01:02:59,300 --> 01:03:00,400
I'm okay.

854
01:03:06,500 --> 01:03:08,700
The Bulls are home tomorrow.
Do you want to go?

855
01:03:15,400 --> 01:03:16,500
Good night.

856
01:03:32,200 --> 01:03:34,600
I'll put an extra blanket there,
just in case.

857
01:03:34,900 --> 01:03:36,500
If he needs one,
he'll ask for it.

858
01:03:36,700 --> 01:03:39,100
He doesn't know how cold
this house gets.

859
01:03:39,400 --> 01:03:41,200
Please relax, honey. Okay?

860
01:03:41,400 --> 01:03:43,500
-Relax. He's home.
-Oh, God.

861
01:03:43,700 --> 01:03:46,100
I just want to go in and look at him.

862
01:05:21,500 --> 01:05:23,100
Here, just wear these.

863
01:05:23,300 --> 01:05:24,500
I hate those.

864
01:05:25,100 --> 01:05:27,800
You loved those socks three days ago.

865
01:05:28,300 --> 01:05:31,000
It's not for church. I want tights.

866
01:05:31,300 --> 01:05:34,500
Pick out whatever you want, but hurry.
I have to get dressed.

867
01:05:34,900 --> 01:05:36,900
Why doesn't he like us?

868
01:05:37,800 --> 01:05:39,000
-Who?
-Ben.

869
01:05:39,700 --> 01:05:40,500
Sam.

870
01:05:41,400 --> 01:05:42,600
He does.

871
01:05:43,500 --> 01:05:45,200
It's just, he's...

872
01:05:50,300 --> 01:05:52,400
Even though he's your brother...

873
01:05:52,700 --> 01:05:54,400
this is all very new for him.

874
01:05:55,200 --> 01:05:56,500
He just needs time to..

875
01:05:57,400 --> 01:05:59,900
He just needs time
to get used to us.

876
01:06:00,200 --> 01:06:01,900
And we have to help him, okay?

877
01:06:05,400 --> 01:06:06,400
Hurry.

878
01:06:25,400 --> 01:06:28,800
Today, we celebrate
the presence among us...

879
01:06:29,000 --> 01:06:30,500
in their wholeness...

880
01:06:30,700 --> 01:06:32,900
of the Cappadora family.

881
01:06:33,100 --> 01:06:36,100
As you all know, their son Ben
was taken from them...

882
01:06:36,900 --> 01:06:38,300
and, by what can only be called...

883
01:06:38,900 --> 01:06:42,600
a modern-day miracle,
returned to them just weeks ago...

884
01:06:43,700 --> 01:06:46,200
not maimed, not torn...

885
01:06:46,400 --> 01:06:48,700
but healthy and whole.

886
01:06:49,100 --> 01:06:51,300
I ask you to join with them today...

887
01:06:51,500 --> 01:06:54,100
in their gratitude and their faith.

888
01:06:55,000 --> 01:06:56,500
I'm also asked to remind you...

889
01:06:56,700 --> 01:06:59,200
of the celebration
at Cappadora's Restaurant...

890
01:06:59,500 --> 01:07:00,800
immediately following the mass.

891
01:07:11,800 --> 01:07:12,700
Are you okay?

892
01:07:13,100 --> 01:07:14,400
Yeah, Dad.

893
01:07:16,000 --> 01:07:18,300
-I'm so happy for you!
-Thank you, Susan.

894
01:07:18,500 --> 01:07:20,000
Congratulations!

895
01:07:23,800 --> 01:07:25,300
That's the big brother.

896
01:07:36,400 --> 01:07:38,200
I want us all to walk in together.

897
01:07:38,500 --> 01:07:41,000
Yes, Mom.
The perfect family.

898
01:08:10,700 --> 01:08:11,800
Welcome home.

899
01:08:12,300 --> 01:08:13,400
Thank you.

900
01:08:13,800 --> 01:08:15,200
The table's here.

901
01:08:41,400 --> 01:08:42,700
Loosen up, man.

902
01:08:52,600 --> 01:08:54,100
I'll show you something.

903
01:09:04,100 --> 01:09:05,600
This is called the tarantella.

904
01:09:05,900 --> 01:09:08,000
It's an Italian dance.
You want to learn it?

905
01:09:08,200 --> 01:09:09,600
You can learn it.

906
01:09:10,300 --> 01:09:13,700
I don't know this dance.
I only know the Hasapiko.

907
01:09:14,000 --> 01:09:16,700
-You'll have to say it again.
-Hasapiko.

908
01:09:17,000 --> 01:09:18,900
Hey, guys, can you hold it?

909
01:09:19,100 --> 01:09:21,000
My son doesn't know the tarantella...

910
01:09:21,200 --> 01:09:23,900
but he knows the Hasapiko.
You know it?

911
01:09:24,100 --> 01:09:26,300
-Of course.
-Great!

912
01:09:47,200 --> 01:09:48,700
I better go up there.

913
01:09:55,000 --> 01:09:56,100
Put your arm out.

914
01:09:57,100 --> 01:09:58,300
Come over here.

915
01:10:02,400 --> 01:10:03,400
Ready?

916
01:10:05,800 --> 01:10:07,100
Right, back...

917
01:10:07,400 --> 01:10:08,600
right, together.

918
01:10:09,000 --> 01:10:10,500
Left, together.

919
01:10:10,800 --> 01:10:13,600
Right, back, right, together.

920
01:11:27,500 --> 01:11:29,700
Yes, Mr. Karras?

921
01:11:30,900 --> 01:11:33,100
I came to bring you Sam's records.

922
01:11:34,100 --> 01:11:35,400
Photos.

923
01:11:38,000 --> 01:11:39,600
This is his...

924
01:11:39,800 --> 01:11:41,400
medical chart.

925
01:11:43,300 --> 01:11:44,900
This is his dental.

926
01:11:46,600 --> 01:11:49,900
One cavity in his permanent teeth
when he was 10.

927
01:11:52,600 --> 01:11:54,400
Report cards...

928
01:11:56,800 --> 01:11:58,100
You'll see.

929
01:11:59,200 --> 01:12:01,100
A little trouble in math.

930
01:12:05,600 --> 01:12:07,000
You know, this...

931
01:12:07,900 --> 01:12:09,800
This was my wife...

932
01:12:10,100 --> 01:12:11,400
and my son.

933
01:12:12,300 --> 01:12:16,100
This wasn't some lunatic
and the boy she kidnapped.

934
01:12:17,300 --> 01:12:18,700
Not to me.

935
01:12:21,100 --> 01:12:22,100
Good night.

936
01:12:35,800 --> 01:12:37,300
What did he want?

937
01:12:53,200 --> 01:12:55,100
We missed a lot of years.

938
01:13:14,200 --> 01:13:15,500
Where you been playing?

939
01:13:15,700 --> 01:13:16,500
City League.

940
01:13:17,200 --> 01:13:18,800
Travelling squad.

941
01:13:19,000 --> 01:13:20,000
First string.

942
01:13:20,200 --> 01:13:21,500
Travelling squad?

943
01:13:21,700 --> 01:13:22,700
My goodness!

944
01:13:22,900 --> 01:13:24,000
Hey, I'm in sixth.

945
01:13:24,200 --> 01:13:26,000
Most of the other guys are in ninth.

946
01:13:26,300 --> 01:13:27,200
It's all about height.

947
01:13:28,100 --> 01:13:28,900
Yeah, sure.

948
01:13:32,300 --> 01:13:33,700
Play Horse?

949
01:13:40,200 --> 01:13:41,700
-That was pretty.
-Not bad.

950
01:13:43,400 --> 01:13:44,200
You on varsity?

951
01:13:45,800 --> 01:13:47,200
I will be.

952
01:13:49,300 --> 01:13:50,700
Coach is such an asshole, though.

953
01:13:52,700 --> 01:13:53,700
Okay, free throw.

954
01:13:58,600 --> 01:14:00,700
-Right here?
-Wherever.

955
01:14:11,300 --> 01:14:14,100
That's an "H".
Get ready for this one.

956
01:14:18,800 --> 01:14:20,300
That's an "O".

957
01:14:20,700 --> 01:14:21,900
I thought this was Horse.

958
01:14:22,500 --> 01:14:24,100
Okay, buddy.

959
01:14:24,600 --> 01:14:25,500
Ready to go downtown?

960
01:14:25,800 --> 01:14:27,200
Wait a second. It's not your shot.

961
01:14:27,400 --> 01:14:28,900
This ain't the city rec, Ben.

962
01:14:29,600 --> 01:14:30,400
It's not "Ben".

963
01:14:30,700 --> 01:14:31,600
Okay...

964
01:14:31,900 --> 01:14:32,800
Ben.

965
01:14:39,800 --> 01:14:41,300
What are we playing to now?

966
01:14:41,600 --> 01:14:42,500
Just play.

967
01:14:52,800 --> 01:14:54,600
Ever seen that
in the city rec, Sammy?

968
01:14:55,600 --> 01:14:56,500
In girls'.

969
01:15:01,200 --> 01:15:02,300
Oh, shit!

970
01:15:02,900 --> 01:15:04,600
I'm sorry, I didn't mean to.

971
01:15:05,100 --> 01:15:07,600
-What's wrong with you?
-Jesus Christ, Dad!

972
01:15:07,800 --> 01:15:08,900
Are you okay? Sure?

973
01:15:10,500 --> 01:15:13,800
Can you go one day without
making some kind of trouble?

974
01:15:14,000 --> 01:15:15,500
What happened to him?

975
01:15:16,300 --> 01:15:18,100
What do you care?

976
01:15:18,600 --> 01:15:20,800
We were just playing ball.

977
01:15:21,800 --> 01:15:24,100
Really. We were just having fun.

978
01:15:49,000 --> 01:15:50,500
And that's Vincent's.

979
01:15:51,300 --> 01:15:52,300
See?

980
01:15:53,700 --> 01:15:55,700
It's his christening gown.

981
01:15:58,800 --> 01:16:02,100
This is what we brought him home
from the hospital in.

982
01:16:05,200 --> 01:16:06,800
Do you want to see yours?

983
01:16:21,300 --> 01:16:22,800
They're so little.

984
01:16:23,500 --> 01:16:25,200
They look like doll clothes.

985
01:16:30,800 --> 01:16:33,100
-What's that smell?
-It's cedar.

986
01:16:33,300 --> 01:16:35,100
It's from the chest.

987
01:16:35,400 --> 01:16:37,600
It's supposed to keep moths away.

988
01:16:37,900 --> 01:16:39,700
Haven't you ever smelled it before?

989
01:16:43,700 --> 01:16:46,300
Maybe my grandmother
had a chest like this.

990
01:16:46,800 --> 01:16:47,700
What?

991
01:16:54,500 --> 01:16:56,700
Are you remembering something?

992
01:17:01,000 --> 01:17:03,400
Beth, can I see my dad today?

993
01:17:04,400 --> 01:17:06,200
I really want to see him.

994
01:17:10,100 --> 01:17:11,200
Sure.

995
01:17:26,600 --> 01:17:30,000
I already told you. That's why
I want to go to my grandma's.

996
01:17:30,300 --> 01:17:33,100
It's what I do for Thanksgiving
every year of my life.

997
01:17:33,300 --> 01:17:34,900
It's a very special day for us.

998
01:17:35,600 --> 01:17:38,200
It's a very special day for us too.

999
01:17:38,400 --> 01:17:40,600
My cousins come, my grandma cooks...

1000
01:17:40,800 --> 01:17:42,300
the whole week before.

1001
01:17:42,500 --> 01:17:44,900
After turkey,
we go outside and play football.

1002
01:17:45,100 --> 01:17:46,700
When we come in,
we have pie...

1003
01:17:47,000 --> 01:17:48,400
and watch TV with my dad.

1004
01:17:49,400 --> 01:17:51,100
The whole family is coming.

1005
01:17:51,400 --> 01:17:53,200
Grandma Rosie, Grandpa Angelo..

1006
01:17:53,400 --> 01:17:55,400
No! I'm not staying here.

1007
01:17:56,800 --> 01:17:58,300
Why do I have to care about them?

1008
01:17:58,500 --> 01:18:00,300
You never even met my grandma.

1009
01:18:00,500 --> 01:18:01,700
You don't like my dad.

1010
01:18:02,000 --> 01:18:03,300
You don't care about what he thinks.

1011
01:18:03,600 --> 01:18:06,400
Of course we like George, Sam.

1012
01:18:06,700 --> 01:18:08,700
Then let me spend
Thanksgiving with him.

1013
01:18:10,800 --> 01:18:12,300
The fact is, you're our son.

1014
01:18:12,500 --> 01:18:16,300
Not George's. This is one thing
we're doing as a family.

1015
01:18:16,500 --> 01:18:19,300
-And it's not negotiable.
-You just want to show me off.

1016
01:18:24,900 --> 01:18:26,000
I'm sorry.

1017
01:18:26,300 --> 01:18:27,700
I didn't mean that.

1018
01:18:33,000 --> 01:18:34,800
Life magazine!
I can't believe...

1019
01:18:35,000 --> 01:18:35,900
the work you're getting.

1020
01:18:36,200 --> 01:18:38,000
You know why I'm getting the work.

1021
01:18:38,200 --> 01:18:39,800
Because you're the best, kiddo.

1022
01:18:40,000 --> 01:18:40,900
Yeah, right.

1023
01:18:41,100 --> 01:18:43,000
Same reason Pat's
restaurant's always full...

1024
01:18:43,300 --> 01:18:45,400
and Vincent's
got a lot of new friends.

1025
01:18:45,600 --> 01:18:47,800
Are you saying it's the celebrity?

1026
01:18:48,400 --> 01:18:50,300
I think the word is "notoriety".

1027
01:18:50,600 --> 01:18:53,300
Where are we eating?
And more to the point, drinking?

1028
01:18:53,600 --> 01:18:54,500
Do you like clams?

1029
01:18:54,700 --> 01:18:55,900
Go this way.

1030
01:18:58,700 --> 01:19:00,900
How's it going with Vincent and Sam?

1031
01:19:06,700 --> 01:19:10,700
Vincent's so busy getting ready for
the basketball tryouts...

1032
01:19:12,200 --> 01:19:13,700
he's ignoring everyone.

1033
01:19:14,000 --> 01:19:16,200
Sam probably thinks....

1034
01:19:17,400 --> 01:19:20,400
I don't know what Sam thinks.
He's still so...

1035
01:19:21,700 --> 01:19:23,000
uncomfortable...

1036
01:19:23,300 --> 01:19:26,700
all the time now.
His grades are falling apart.

1037
01:19:27,300 --> 01:19:28,800
I don't know.

1038
01:19:29,000 --> 01:19:30,900
Well, what's Pat say?

1039
01:19:31,200 --> 01:19:34,800
You know Pat.
He thinks Sam's going to be fine.

1040
01:19:35,000 --> 01:19:37,600
He thinks everything's
going to be fine.

1041
01:19:38,000 --> 01:19:39,400
And what do you think?

1042
01:19:40,500 --> 01:19:41,800
I don't know.

1043
01:19:46,800 --> 01:19:48,900
It's just going to take some time.

1044
01:19:59,200 --> 01:20:03,000
Do you know what the
great Chicago fire of 1871 is?

1045
01:20:05,600 --> 01:20:07,600
Peshtigo, there was
an even worse fire...

1046
01:20:07,900 --> 01:20:09,600
in the same year on the same day.

1047
01:20:10,600 --> 01:20:12,600
Every single building
in the town burned.

1048
01:20:12,900 --> 01:20:13,700
Hundreds of people died.

1049
01:20:14,000 --> 01:20:15,500
But Chicago was a big city...

1050
01:20:15,700 --> 01:20:18,100
so that's the fire
everybody paid attention to.

1051
01:20:20,000 --> 01:20:22,800
There's a beautiful graveyard.
I want to get some shots.

1052
01:20:38,900 --> 01:20:40,200
Basically...

1053
01:20:40,400 --> 01:20:44,300
it's the story of what happened.
What we talked about in the car.

1054
01:20:52,700 --> 01:20:55,100
Look at this, Sam.
He was only 14 years old.

1055
01:20:55,400 --> 01:20:57,100
That must've been so sad.

1056
01:20:58,500 --> 01:21:00,700
But look, 1869.

1057
01:21:00,900 --> 01:21:03,100
He died two years before the fire.

1058
01:21:03,400 --> 01:21:05,900
Maybe he killed himself,
like my mom.

1059
01:21:06,400 --> 01:21:08,100
I mean, Cecilia.

1060
01:21:11,800 --> 01:21:13,100
Why do you think that?

1061
01:21:13,400 --> 01:21:15,000
Here, look through here.

1062
01:21:16,200 --> 01:21:19,700
Like, for Cecilia,
I think she was just too sad.

1063
01:21:21,500 --> 01:21:22,900
So maybe this guy was...

1064
01:21:23,100 --> 01:21:25,000
too sad too, you know?

1065
01:21:25,200 --> 01:21:26,400
What do you mean?

1066
01:21:27,600 --> 01:21:30,200
There could be worse things
than being dead.

1067
01:21:32,900 --> 01:21:33,900
Like what?

1068
01:21:40,500 --> 01:21:42,200
You know how much we love you.

1069
01:21:42,400 --> 01:21:43,800
Yeah, I know you do...

1070
01:21:44,000 --> 01:21:46,400
and Pat and Kerry.

1071
01:21:46,700 --> 01:21:48,100
And Vincent too.

1072
01:21:49,300 --> 01:21:50,200
Yeah, right.

1073
01:21:50,500 --> 01:21:53,000
Really, he's like that with all of us.

1074
01:21:55,500 --> 01:21:57,300
He's had a hard time.

1075
01:21:57,600 --> 01:21:59,100
What about me?

1076
01:21:59,600 --> 01:22:01,300
I love my dad.

1077
01:22:01,600 --> 01:22:03,700
And I loved my mom too.

1078
01:22:04,000 --> 01:22:05,800
She didn't mean to be sick.

1079
01:22:06,000 --> 01:22:09,100
Why do I have to be punished
when it wasn't my fault?

1080
01:22:19,400 --> 01:22:22,400
Do you know how much
I've missed holding you...

1081
01:22:22,600 --> 01:22:24,500
all these years?

1082
01:22:25,200 --> 01:22:28,300
And how many years
you didn't have me to hug you?

1083
01:22:29,900 --> 01:22:31,500
They hugged me.

1084
01:22:33,400 --> 01:22:35,200
They hugged me all the time.

1085
01:22:50,300 --> 01:22:51,800
Sam, what do you wish?

1086
01:22:54,500 --> 01:22:56,100
You can say.

1087
01:22:57,500 --> 01:22:59,900
That everything was
like it was before.

1088
01:23:00,700 --> 01:23:04,600
But that would hurt you and Pat,
and I couldn't stand that either.

1089
01:23:07,200 --> 01:23:08,600
I don't know.

1090
01:23:33,100 --> 01:23:34,900
-Sam's gone.
-What do you mean?

1091
01:23:35,100 --> 01:23:37,500
He's not in his room.
I can't find him.

1092
01:23:37,900 --> 01:23:40,700
-Did you look downstairs?
-He's not there. I can't find him.

1093
01:23:40,900 --> 01:23:43,200
-Did you talk to Vincent?
-He's asleep. His door's locked.

1094
01:23:43,500 --> 01:23:45,800
-What about Kerry?
-She's asleep too.

1095
01:24:00,000 --> 01:24:02,000
I'm sorry.
He did it again.

1096
01:24:04,300 --> 01:24:05,300
What'd he do?

1097
01:24:05,500 --> 01:24:08,100
He's been sneaking out
and coming to my house.

1098
01:24:08,400 --> 01:24:10,700
He crawls into his old bed
and sleeps.

1099
01:24:11,500 --> 01:24:13,700
Vincent told me he knew all about it.

1100
01:24:15,200 --> 01:24:17,400
-You knew?
-I brought him back, didn't I?

1101
01:24:19,800 --> 01:24:21,400
How long has this been going on?

1102
01:24:21,700 --> 01:24:23,000
Not that long.

1103
01:24:23,400 --> 01:24:25,200
I had a feeling something
was wrong, so this time...

1104
01:24:25,500 --> 01:24:26,600
I brought him back myself.

1105
01:24:27,500 --> 01:24:28,900
You knew and didn't tell me?

1106
01:24:29,500 --> 01:24:30,700
He's home, okay?

1107
01:24:30,900 --> 01:24:32,200
This time, anyhow.

1108
01:24:35,400 --> 01:24:37,000
-Go up to your room.
-Why?

1109
01:24:37,300 --> 01:24:39,600
-What did I do?
-You ran away!

1110
01:24:39,900 --> 01:24:41,700
You scared the hell
out of your mom and me!

1111
01:24:42,000 --> 01:24:44,200
That's not going to happen.
You understand me?

1112
01:24:44,400 --> 01:24:47,200
No, I don't understand.
I'm sick of this whole thing!

1113
01:24:47,500 --> 01:24:51,300
I don't see why I have to live
two blocks from my own house.

1114
01:24:51,600 --> 01:24:53,400
I've been trying for three months.

1115
01:24:53,600 --> 01:24:55,200
Three months!

1116
01:24:55,600 --> 01:24:57,900
You want me to come home,
Dad, right?

1117
01:24:58,400 --> 01:24:59,400
Come on, tell them.

1118
01:25:03,200 --> 01:25:05,900
He's been asking me
why can't he live with me.

1119
01:25:06,200 --> 01:25:08,900
I told him what
his mother did was very wrong.

1120
01:25:09,100 --> 01:25:10,800
She didn't know what she was doing.

1121
01:25:11,400 --> 01:25:12,700
She was sick.

1122
01:25:14,200 --> 01:25:16,900
We know how hard
this has been for you.

1123
01:25:17,200 --> 01:25:19,100
We know how much you miss George.

1124
01:25:19,300 --> 01:25:21,100
But this is your home.

1125
01:25:21,700 --> 01:25:23,600
Sam, go upstairs now.

1126
01:25:24,900 --> 01:25:25,900
I hate you.

1127
01:25:26,200 --> 01:25:27,300
I hate all of you!

1128
01:25:27,600 --> 01:25:30,100
You too, Dad,
and I'm never coming back!

1129
01:25:35,400 --> 01:25:37,600
Jesus, I want to do right by him.

1130
01:25:38,700 --> 01:25:40,800
I want him to be happy.

1131
01:25:41,000 --> 01:25:42,900
If you can give him
the family he deserves...

1132
01:25:43,100 --> 01:25:44,900
goddamn it, you give him that!

1133
01:25:48,500 --> 01:25:51,200
But I've never seen him
like this before.

1134
01:25:51,900 --> 01:25:54,300
He's never been sad more than
a day in his life.

1135
01:25:54,900 --> 01:25:57,600
Right now, he's the saddest boy
in the world.

1136
01:26:35,000 --> 01:26:38,300
You know, what happened last night,
that's just the tip of it.

1137
01:26:44,200 --> 01:26:46,700
I'm going to say this just once.

1138
01:26:47,000 --> 01:26:47,900
I love you.

1139
01:26:49,100 --> 01:26:51,800
I've been in love with you
your whole life.

1140
01:26:52,300 --> 01:26:54,300
But you know what
I've seen about you?

1141
01:26:55,600 --> 01:26:57,500
You've made a career
out of being unhappy.

1142
01:26:58,500 --> 01:27:00,700
-That is not fair.
-But I'm not like that.

1143
01:27:01,900 --> 01:27:05,100
If I have a chance to be happy,
I'm going to be happy.

1144
01:27:06,500 --> 01:27:09,200
Can't you just try
and let us all be happy?

1145
01:27:09,800 --> 01:27:10,800
What about Sam?

1146
01:27:11,100 --> 01:27:12,900
Just keep being a mother to him.

1147
01:27:13,200 --> 01:27:14,500
Help him get through this.

1148
01:27:14,700 --> 01:27:16,700
He doesn't know who we are.

1149
01:27:17,400 --> 01:27:19,500
He doesn't remember us.

1150
01:27:21,700 --> 01:27:24,100
We are holding him against his will.

1151
01:27:24,300 --> 01:27:25,800
Where are you going with this?

1152
01:27:26,200 --> 01:27:29,000
If you think I'm going to
lose my kid again..

1153
01:27:29,300 --> 01:27:31,400
I can't ignore that
because you finally...

1154
01:27:31,700 --> 01:27:33,800
have your life the way you want it.

1155
01:27:34,200 --> 01:27:36,200
It's like we are the kidnappers now.

1156
01:27:36,400 --> 01:27:37,700
We're not the kidnappers!

1157
01:27:38,000 --> 01:27:40,100
Sam will be fine.
He'll get through this.

1158
01:27:40,300 --> 01:27:41,400
It's you!

1159
01:27:41,600 --> 01:27:44,200
Losing your kid once
wasn't enough, was it?

1160
01:27:44,400 --> 01:27:45,600
You know something?

1161
01:27:46,000 --> 01:27:47,000
You're right.

1162
01:27:47,300 --> 01:27:49,600
I wasn't there.
I let it happen.

1163
01:27:50,000 --> 01:27:53,200
It only took a minute,
and we've paid for it.

1164
01:27:53,400 --> 01:27:55,000
I have and you have...

1165
01:27:55,200 --> 01:27:58,400
and Vincent has,
but I don't think that means...

1166
01:27:58,700 --> 01:28:01,400
that Sam has to pay for it too.
Does it?

1167
01:28:02,500 --> 01:28:04,700
We are where we are.

1168
01:28:04,900 --> 01:28:07,900
How we got here doesn't matter.
What matters is...

1169
01:28:09,800 --> 01:28:11,300
what do we do now?

1170
01:28:15,600 --> 01:28:17,800
Don't push me on this, Beth.

1171
01:28:20,900 --> 01:28:22,700
I want to give him back.

1172
01:28:23,600 --> 01:28:25,400
I can't do that.

1173
01:28:28,900 --> 01:28:32,100
Then I want you to let me do
what I have to do.

1174
01:30:03,500 --> 01:30:05,600
Can you get your bags okay?

1175
01:32:42,000 --> 01:32:44,400
I'll try Jay again,
but if we can't get him out...

1176
01:32:44,600 --> 01:32:47,100
for the weekend,
I won't have a problem.

1177
01:32:47,300 --> 01:32:49,100
Don't you think
he's been through enough?

1178
01:32:49,400 --> 01:32:50,800
Something's got to
get his attention.

1179
01:32:51,000 --> 01:32:53,300
Maybe he's doing this to get
your attention.

1180
01:32:53,600 --> 01:32:56,200
Candy, he's always had my attention.

1181
01:33:06,300 --> 01:33:08,800
He is so angry with me.

1182
01:33:10,300 --> 01:33:11,900
Things are really bad.

1183
01:33:12,100 --> 01:33:14,600
I know.
But I think he's right about Vincent.

1184
01:33:14,800 --> 01:33:17,100
I can't win with Vincent.
He hates me.

1185
01:33:17,400 --> 01:33:21,100
He doesn't hate you. What are you
talking about? He loves you.

1186
01:33:21,300 --> 01:33:24,000
Have you never seen the way
that he looks at you?

1187
01:33:24,300 --> 01:33:26,400
All he wants you to do
is to forgive him.

1188
01:33:26,700 --> 01:33:28,000
Forgive him?

1189
01:33:28,500 --> 01:33:33,100
For all the shit he's pulled and
the shit you don't know he's pulled.

1190
01:33:33,300 --> 01:33:37,000
He's so much like you.
He takes everything onto himself.

1191
01:33:37,900 --> 01:33:40,800
How do you think he's
feeling now that Sam is gone?

1192
01:34:17,100 --> 01:34:18,300
You okay?

1193
01:34:18,900 --> 01:34:20,300
I'm fine.

1194
01:34:25,200 --> 01:34:26,900
Do you need anything?

1195
01:34:27,700 --> 01:34:30,600
I think you'll have to
stay here another day or so.

1196
01:34:30,900 --> 01:34:31,900
It's the weekend.

1197
01:34:32,100 --> 01:34:33,300
I'm fine.

1198
01:34:35,000 --> 01:34:36,800
Headache. It's no big deal.

1199
01:34:41,900 --> 01:34:44,000
Do you know how lucky you were?

1200
01:34:44,800 --> 01:34:46,800
Mr. Teeter's car was totalled.

1201
01:34:47,500 --> 01:34:50,600
-You could've been..
-I don't need this right now.

1202
01:34:52,300 --> 01:34:53,500
What are you doing here?

1203
01:34:54,400 --> 01:34:56,800
I've been doing fine without you.

1204
01:35:00,100 --> 01:35:02,500
I don't think you have been.

1205
01:35:05,300 --> 01:35:06,600
I'm sorry.

1206
01:35:31,800 --> 01:35:34,200
We're going to get you out of here.

1207
01:35:35,400 --> 01:35:37,200
Dad's working on it.

1208
01:35:52,700 --> 01:35:54,100
Pat? Jay just called.

1209
01:35:54,400 --> 01:35:57,300
He says we can pick Vincent up
in the morning.

1210
01:35:58,000 --> 01:36:00,400
All right. Thank you.

1211
01:36:15,800 --> 01:36:17,300
Can't we get past this?

1212
01:36:19,600 --> 01:36:21,800
This isn't just about losing Sam.

1213
01:36:23,200 --> 01:36:25,000
What is it about?

1214
01:36:25,900 --> 01:36:27,000
Listen to me.

1215
01:36:28,100 --> 01:36:30,300
The Sam that's in your head...

1216
01:36:30,500 --> 01:36:32,100
he doesn't exist.

1217
01:36:33,700 --> 01:36:36,000
The family that's in your head...

1218
01:36:36,400 --> 01:36:37,600
doesn't exist either.

1219
01:36:39,000 --> 01:36:40,700
This family is not in my head.

1220
01:36:40,900 --> 01:36:42,600
It's very real.

1221
01:36:42,900 --> 01:36:44,100
It's you and me...

1222
01:36:44,300 --> 01:36:45,400
and Kerry and Vincent.

1223
01:36:45,600 --> 01:36:48,100
After what he pulled,
I pray I find a way...

1224
01:36:48,400 --> 01:36:50,700
to get him through high school
in one piece...

1225
01:36:51,000 --> 01:36:54,200
and get him to believe he can
get through life without fouling up!

1226
01:36:54,500 --> 01:36:55,700
You are right.

1227
01:36:55,900 --> 01:36:59,000
You're right about Vincent,
but you're wrong about Sam.

1228
01:36:59,300 --> 01:37:02,300
You don't know him.
You don't want to know him.

1229
01:37:04,200 --> 01:37:07,100
And you don't know me anymore either.

1230
01:37:08,200 --> 01:37:09,600
I have known you..

1231
01:37:09,900 --> 01:37:12,000
Part of you liked it
when I was falling apart...

1232
01:37:12,300 --> 01:37:14,300
and you were holding
this family together...

1233
01:37:15,000 --> 01:37:17,200
making the decisions.
But now...

1234
01:37:17,400 --> 01:37:19,700
I don't need you
to pull me out of bed...

1235
01:37:20,000 --> 01:37:22,200
and make me pay attention
to the kids.

1236
01:37:25,400 --> 01:37:26,800
I have to go to work.

1237
01:37:28,100 --> 01:37:29,800
But I do need you.

1238
01:37:30,700 --> 01:37:31,500
Why?

1239
01:37:31,800 --> 01:37:33,300
Tell me what for.

1240
01:37:34,400 --> 01:37:36,300
I need you to love me.

1241
01:37:53,400 --> 01:37:54,800
You got a visitor.

1242
01:37:55,600 --> 01:37:58,200
Everyone I've ever met
in my life has already been here.

1243
01:37:58,500 --> 01:37:59,500
Name's Sam Karras.

1244
01:38:01,000 --> 01:38:02,700
You gonna see him or not?

1245
01:38:16,300 --> 01:38:17,200
So...

1246
01:38:17,800 --> 01:38:19,000
you okay?

1247
01:38:19,400 --> 01:38:22,000
They gave me 5 to 10.
But I'm reasonably okay.

1248
01:38:22,400 --> 01:38:23,700
I'm kidding.

1249
01:38:25,200 --> 01:38:26,100
Were you drunk?

1250
01:38:26,900 --> 01:38:28,600
I was over-served.

1251
01:38:29,000 --> 01:38:31,100
Yeah, Sam, I was drunk.

1252
01:38:32,000 --> 01:38:33,300
So what do you want?

1253
01:38:34,900 --> 01:38:36,300
I just thought....

1254
01:38:37,500 --> 01:38:39,600
I thought we could be friends.

1255
01:38:40,200 --> 01:38:41,300
Friends?

1256
01:38:41,800 --> 01:38:44,100
Tell me how we can be friends.

1257
01:38:44,400 --> 01:38:46,600
You come back. You leave.

1258
01:38:46,800 --> 01:38:48,200
You go in and out our window.

1259
01:38:48,500 --> 01:38:49,700
I don't know you, Ben.

1260
01:38:50,000 --> 01:38:52,200
Sam! Whatever your name is.

1261
01:38:52,600 --> 01:38:54,700
You're a concept. You follow me?

1262
01:38:55,000 --> 01:38:56,800
-That's not my fault.
-"Not my fault!"

1263
01:38:57,100 --> 01:39:00,400
You always whine about
whose fault it is. Who cares?

1264
01:39:01,200 --> 01:39:03,200
Look, I got my own life now.

1265
01:39:04,100 --> 01:39:07,600
It's pretty un-fun at the moment.
Tell me what you want.

1266
01:39:09,400 --> 01:39:10,900
You're my brother.

1267
01:39:11,600 --> 01:39:12,900
I missed you.

1268
01:39:14,200 --> 01:39:17,000
Sometimes, I even thought
I shouldn't have.

1269
01:39:19,100 --> 01:39:21,000
Whatever, you're my brother.

1270
01:39:24,600 --> 01:39:26,400
You should go now, Sam.

1271
01:39:27,700 --> 01:39:29,800
I'm sorry. You're a good kid.

1272
01:39:30,100 --> 01:39:31,500
You're fine, but I'm..

1273
01:39:32,500 --> 01:39:35,800
-Maybe I'll visit you when I'm out..
-Wait!

1274
01:39:37,000 --> 01:39:38,700
I gotta tell you something.

1275
01:39:40,100 --> 01:39:42,000
I remembered something.

1276
01:39:42,500 --> 01:39:43,600
What do you mean?

1277
01:39:44,400 --> 01:39:46,500
Well, when I was at your house...

1278
01:39:46,700 --> 01:39:48,800
Beth showed me this old trunk.

1279
01:39:49,100 --> 01:39:50,800
It was full of old baby clothes.

1280
01:39:51,300 --> 01:39:52,800
I didn't remember anything.

1281
01:39:53,100 --> 01:39:54,500
Yeah. So?

1282
01:39:54,900 --> 01:39:56,400
But I remembered the smell.

1283
01:39:56,900 --> 01:39:58,700
From being inside the trunk.

1284
01:39:59,200 --> 01:40:00,500
Hide-and-seek.

1285
01:40:03,400 --> 01:40:04,800
Did that really happen?

1286
01:40:05,100 --> 01:40:06,100
Yeah.

1287
01:40:07,100 --> 01:40:09,700
You let the lid shut and it caught.

1288
01:40:11,100 --> 01:40:12,300
I knew it.

1289
01:40:12,700 --> 01:40:14,100
I knew it!

1290
01:40:14,600 --> 01:40:16,500
Finally, you came
and opened the top.

1291
01:40:16,800 --> 01:40:18,300
You were just there.

1292
01:40:19,900 --> 01:40:21,600
Not scared or anything.

1293
01:40:21,900 --> 01:40:23,700
See? That's what I remember.

1294
01:40:24,000 --> 01:40:24,900
What?

1295
01:40:25,100 --> 01:40:26,800
That I wasn't scared.

1296
01:40:27,300 --> 01:40:29,300
Because I knew you'd come
and find me.

1297
01:41:06,800 --> 01:41:08,500
What the hell are you doing?

1298
01:41:10,000 --> 01:41:10,800
Nothing.

1299
01:41:11,400 --> 01:41:12,300
Want to play?

1300
01:41:12,600 --> 01:41:15,300
It's midnight and it's cold,
in case you haven't noticed.

1301
01:41:16,500 --> 01:41:17,500
Yeah. So?

1302
01:41:18,400 --> 01:41:21,400
Jesus, Sam!
Does George know you're here?

1303
01:41:22,000 --> 01:41:22,900
Yeah.

1304
01:41:23,200 --> 01:41:24,100
Come on down.

1305
01:41:24,800 --> 01:41:27,300
You just want to get me
arrested again, don't you?

1306
01:41:27,500 --> 01:41:29,500
Ever heard of disturbing the peace?

1307
01:41:31,800 --> 01:41:33,300
We could play quiet.

1308
01:41:34,800 --> 01:41:36,600
What's the matter? Come on!

1309
01:41:38,500 --> 01:41:39,600
All right.

1310
01:41:55,700 --> 01:41:57,100
What are you waiting for?

1311
01:41:57,400 --> 01:41:59,100
-Easy, Sam.
-All right.

1312
01:41:59,300 --> 01:42:01,800
Losers out to 11, win by 2?

1313
01:42:02,600 --> 01:42:05,000
What's the matter?
You asleep or something?

1314
01:42:12,900 --> 01:42:14,200
This way?

1315
01:42:14,500 --> 01:42:15,700
Which way?

1316
01:42:16,900 --> 01:42:18,400
Quit fouling me!

1317
01:42:38,900 --> 01:42:41,700
You got to say, "beat".
You are beat, right?

1318
01:42:42,300 --> 01:42:43,800
I let you.

1319
01:42:44,400 --> 01:42:45,600
Sure.

1320
01:42:46,200 --> 01:42:47,400
Let's call it a night.

1321
01:42:48,100 --> 01:42:50,200
Come back tomorrow for a rematch.

1322
01:42:51,800 --> 01:42:55,100
Well, the thing is, I'm not going back.

1323
01:42:57,800 --> 01:42:58,900
What do you mean?

1324
01:43:03,200 --> 01:43:04,500
What are you doing?

1325
01:43:05,400 --> 01:43:06,900
George knows.

1326
01:43:07,600 --> 01:43:09,800
We talked about it
a lot last week.

1327
01:43:10,500 --> 01:43:12,100
He knows why
I came here so late.

1328
01:43:12,300 --> 01:43:13,600
Which is why?

1329
01:43:14,700 --> 01:43:17,600
I didn't want to have this
whole big thing with you...

1330
01:43:17,800 --> 01:43:19,900
and Beth and Pat.

1331
01:43:23,000 --> 01:43:24,200
Sam?

1332
01:43:27,000 --> 01:43:29,000
Is this permanent?

1333
01:43:30,000 --> 01:43:31,400
I don't know.

1334
01:43:32,400 --> 01:43:33,800
I mean, maybe.

1335
01:43:34,700 --> 01:43:36,100
If I can.

1336
01:43:44,200 --> 01:43:47,200
Jesus, what is this,
your cinder block collection?

1337
01:43:55,300 --> 01:43:56,900
I was the one.

1338
01:43:58,400 --> 01:44:00,300
I let go of your hand.

1339
01:44:02,700 --> 01:44:04,500
This thing is heavy.

1340
01:44:04,900 --> 01:44:05,900
My dad..

1341
01:44:06,200 --> 01:44:08,800
-George helped me carry it.
-Did you hear what I said?

1342
01:44:10,500 --> 01:44:12,200
Yeah. So what?

1343
01:44:13,000 --> 01:44:14,900
I let go of your hand, Sam.

1344
01:44:16,500 --> 01:44:18,300
I told you to get lost.
That's what I said.

1345
01:44:18,500 --> 01:44:21,100
-I said, "Get lost!"
-Big deal.

1346
01:44:21,300 --> 01:44:24,500
Everybody says stuff like that.
"Get lost!"

1347
01:44:26,200 --> 01:44:28,500
Here's the deal.
Make it-take it to 11.

1348
01:44:28,700 --> 01:44:30,400
Gotta win by two.

1349
01:44:31,000 --> 01:44:32,500
Loser carries it up alone.

1350
01:44:35,600 --> 01:44:37,000
Come on, man!

1351
01:44:37,300 --> 01:44:38,900
Are you too tired to play?

1352
01:44:40,700 --> 01:44:41,900
Come on, let's go.

1353
01:44:45,300 --> 01:44:47,500
They'll wake up the neighbourhood.

1354
01:44:47,800 --> 01:44:49,300
Let them play.

1355
01:44:56,400 --> 01:44:57,900
I just..

1356
01:45:00,100 --> 01:45:02,100
Let's get some sleep.

1357
01:45:17,200 --> 01:45:18,600
Right there!

1358
01:45:23,800 --> 01:45:25,500
I'm just warming up.

1359
